1 olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 carrot
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ lemon
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Middle Eastern Seasoning
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
½ tbs honey
1 bag baby spinach leaves

• Preheat oven to 220ºC/200ºC fan-forced.
• Cut cauliflower into small florets. Cut carrot into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over garlic & herb seasoning, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender and brown around edges, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, zest lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt and lemon zest. Season to taste and set aside.

TIP: Add more or less lemon zest to taste.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, Middle Eastern seasoning, fine breadcrumbs, the egg and a generous pinch of salt.
• Using damp hands, roll beef mixture into small koftas (3 per person).

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook beef koftas, turning, until browned and cooked through, 10-12 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey, turning koftas to coat.

• When the veggies are done, remove the tray from oven, then add baby spinach leaves and a generous squeeze of lemon juice.
• Toss to combine and season to taste.

• Divide garlic-herb roast veggie toss between plates. Top with Middle Eastern beef koftas.
• Dollop over lemon yoghurt and serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!